  "prompt": "Where can I find affordable cake shops on the Gold Coast?",
  "response": "Finding affordable cake shops on the Gold Coast can be a fun adventure! Here are some suggestions to help you discover great spots:\n\n### 1. **Local Bakeries**\n   - **Miss Moneypenny\u2019s Cakes & Catering**: Known for quality and affordability, they offer a range of cakes for all occasions.\n   - **The Cake That Ate Paris**: This caf\u00e9 and bakery is famous for its delicious and reasonably priced cakes.\n   - **Cake Haven**: A cozy spot offering custom cakes at great prices.\n\n### 2. **Cafes with Cake Options**\n   - **Bam Bam Bakehouse**: While known for pastries, they also have delightful cakes at reasonable prices.\n   - **Paddock Bakery**: Offers a variety of baked goods, including cakes, in a charming setting.\n\n### 3. **Supermarkets and Chains**\n   - **Woolworths** or **Coles**: These supermarkets often have affordable pre-made cakes that are surprisingly good.\n   - **Cheesecake Shop**: A chain known for its affordable and tasty cakes, with multiple locations on the Gold Coast.\n\n### 4. **Markets**\n   - **The Village Markets (Burleigh Heads)** or **Broadbeach Markets**: Local bakers often sell cakes and desserts at great prices.\n\n### 5. **Asian Bakeries**\n   - **BreadTop**: Offers a variety of Asian-style cakes and pastries at affordable prices.\n   - **85 Degrees Bakery Cafe**: Known for its light and fluffy cakes at reasonable prices.\n\n### 6. **Online Options**\n   - **Facebook Marketplace** or **Gumtree**: Local bakers often advertise their services here.\n   - **Instagram or Facebook**: Search for local bakers who might offer affordable custom cakes.\n\n### Tips:\n- Check for daily specials or discounts.\n- Order in advance for custom cakes to avoid rush fees.\n- Consider smaller or family-run bakeries for personalized service and better deals.\n\nEnjoy your cake hunt on the Gold Coast! \ud83c\udf82",
